.TH tg-exec 1 "November 2025" "tg-exec 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tg-exec \- run a command and notify Telegram (Go)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tg-exec
[command ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Executes a command, prints output to terminal (tee), and sends a Telegram notification.
Includes full output only on failure.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Global: /etc/tg-exec/config.conf
User: ~/.config/tg-exec/config.conf
.SH ENV
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID, TG_NOTE, TG_EXEC_ALWAYS, TG_EXEC_PARSE_MODE, TG_EXEC_TZ, TG_EXEC_HTTP_TIMEOUT, TG_EXEC_RETRIES, TG_EXEC_BACKOFF, TG_EXEC_STRICT.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns the exit code of the executed command; 70 if notification fails and TG_EXEC_STRICT=1.
